Warlocks are hex-based casters who evolved from cipher shadow-workers who discovered resonance in dark spaces between their strikes.
The tradition's foundation is shadow compacts: working relationships with poorly understood entities that may be spirits, entropy principles, or Black Sun Shard fragments.
Hex craft attacks indirectly by undermining systems the target depends on: protection wards, combat reflexes, stable footing, concentration.
Combat role is debuffer and indirect-damage caster who degrades opponent capability before and during engagement.
Key abilities include hex craft, shadow compacts, ward disruption, and curse application.
Every hex carries a price from the compact entity, described variously as attention, resonance debt, or deepening relationship.
The tradition's methodology for managing the price is harm-reduction focused: understanding costs and monitoring sustainable rates.
Warlocks share foundational skills with the Cipher tradition.
The Nightblade class synthesizes Warlock hex and shadow arts with Assassin precision methodology.
